If you have two items, you end up comparing them and swapping if
necessary:

0---o---+
    |
1---o---+

If you have four items, you do more compares and swaps:

    A   B     C
0---o---o---------+
    |   |
1---o---|-o---o---+
        | |   |
2---o---o-|---o---+
    |     |
3---o-----o-------+

The A series ensures that the smaller of each pair is on the even line
and the larger on the odd line.  The B series ensures that the smallest
value is on 0 and the largest value is on 3.  The C series ensures that
the middle values are in order.

If you have 8 items, you have still more work to do.

